FBIS3-1259 "drafr057_e_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Mar 1994 WEST AFRICA Senegal Parties Sign Mobilization Against Violence Pact LD2303133494 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 GMT 23 Mar 94 LD2303133494 Paris Radio France International Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] An agreement for mobilization against violence has been signed by 16 political parties in Senegal. This mobilization comes in the wake of the bloody demonstration that took place in Dakar last month, where members of the security forces were killed in cold blood. Amath Dansokho, a government minister [of urban planning and housing] and an opposition leader, is one of the signatories of the agreement: [Begin Dansokho recording] It is necessary to put an end to this drift. It is extremely serious, because one has to realize that we have very fragile states, and, should there be any illusion as to the Senegalese peculiarity, I think that everything has now [word indistinct]. It is necessary to face facts: If we carry on like this, we are going to lose our country. This is a call to all democrats in Senegal, to all those concerned about civilian peace, to all those concerned about a civilized political life and who oppose a barbarous drift, because it is us. This is the way things go in Africa. [end recording]
